summaries.full: With the papers signed, Biriba and Vini start going through the pains of building a startup. Vini enlists their new financial manager Digao to help find a supplier before it’s too late, while Salim attempts to keep Biriba entrenched in the illicit drug market.

summaries.full: Biriba and Vini are officially in business but they still have a lot to learn about the product Joselo is supplying them. Salim shares big news with Biriba in a step towards reconciliation, while Piolho hatches a scheme to move up the ranks at the smoke hole.

summaries.short: Series premiere. Biriba is a lowly but talented drug dealer whose future is disrupted by the legalization of weed in Brazil.
summaries.full: Series premiere. Biriba is a lowly but talented drug dealer whose future is disrupted by the legalization of weed in Brazil. His best friend Salim wants him to become a bigger player in their current criminal enterprise, but his client Vini presents the possibility of becoming a legitimate businessman.
